Note:
==============================================================================
GRAPHEME - User-Perceived Character Cluster Primitive
==============================================================================

A Grapheme is a sequence of one or more Unicode codepoints that together
form a single user-perceived "character". Examples:

    "e" + U+0301 COMBINING ACUTE  ->  one grapheme "é"
    "🇺" + "🇸"                     ->  one grapheme "🇺🇸"
    "👨" + ZWJ + "👩" + ZWJ + "👧"  ->  one grapheme "family emoji"

Grapheme cluster breaking follows the rules in UAX #29
(https://www.unicode.org/reports/tr29/), specifically the
"extended grapheme cluster" definition which is the de-facto standard
for user-visible text segmentation.

Memory layout for a Grapheme (16 bytes):
  offset 0:  data pointer (Integer, 8 bytes) - UTF-8 bytes of cluster
  offset 8:  byte_length   (Integer, 8 bytes)

The pure-Runa baseline implements the boundary rules using a state
machine over UAX #29 grapheme break properties. The supporting
property tables are minimal in the v0.0.8.5 baseline; full coverage
ships with the v0.2.x table generator. The implementation always
returns a SAFE boundary - it may over-segment (treat one cluster as
multiple) but it never UNDER-segments (merging clusters that should
be separate). Over-segmentation is acceptable for stdlib use today
and is corrected as the tables fill in.
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StrCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/text/codepoint.runa" as CP

Constant GRAPHEME_HEADER_SIZE as Integer is 16
Constant GRAPHEME_OFFSET_DATA as Integer is 0
Constant GRAPHEME_OFFSET_LENGTH as Integer is 8

Note: UAX #29 grapheme break properties used by the state machine
Constant GBP_OTHER as Integer is 0
Constant GBP_CR as Integer is 1
Constant GBP_LF as Integer is 2
Constant GBP_CONTROL as Integer is 3
Constant GBP_EXTEND as Integer is 4
Constant GBP_ZWJ as Integer is 5
Constant GBP_REGIONAL_INDICATOR as Integer is 6
Constant GBP_PREPEND as Integer is 7
Constant GBP_SPACINGMARK as Integer is 8
Constant GBP_L as Integer is 9
Constant GBP_V as Integer is 10
Constant GBP_T as Integer is 11
Constant GBP_LV as Integer is 12
Constant GBP_LVT as Integer is 13
Constant GBP_EXTENDED_PICTOGRAPHIC as Integer is 14

Note: ============================================================================
Note: GRAPHEME BREAK PROPERTY LOOKUP
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "grapheme_break_property" takes cp as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
        Maps a codepoint to its UAX #29 grapheme cluster break property.
        Covers the classifications needed by the state machine: line
        terminators, combining marks, ZWJ, regional indicators, Hangul
        jamo sequences, and extended pictographs.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
        Range tests grouped by property. Out-of-range and unknown
        codepoints default to GBP_OTHER.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
        Short-circuits on early ASCII checks.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
        Pure classification.
    @End Security_Scope

    If cp is equal to 13:
        Return GBP_CR
    End If
    If cp is equal to 10:
        Return GBP_LF
    End If
    If cp is less than 32:
        Return GBP_CONTROL
    End If
    If cp is equal to 127:
        Return GBP_CONTROL
    End If
    If cp is greater than or equal to 128:
        If cp is less than or equal to 159:
            Return GBP_CONTROL
        End If
    End If
    Note: ZERO WIDTH JOINER U+200D
    If cp is equal to 8205:
        Return GBP_ZWJ
    End If
    Note: ZERO WIDTH NON-JOINER U+200C is Extend, not separate ZWNJ
    If cp is equal to 8204:
        Return GBP_EXTEND
    End If
    Note: Combining Diacritical Marks U+0300..U+036F (Extend)
    If cp is greater than or equal to 768:
        If cp is less than or equal to 879:
            Return GBP_EXTEND
        End If
    End If
    Note: Variation Selectors U+FE00..U+FE0F (Extend)
    If cp is greater than or equal to 65024:
        If cp is less than or equal to 65039:
            Return GBP_EXTEND
        End If
    End If
    Note: Combining Diacritical Marks Supplement U+1DC0..U+1DFF (Extend)
    If cp is greater than or equal to 7616:
        If cp is less than or equal to 7679:
            Return GBP_EXTEND
        End If
    End If
    Note: Combining Diacritical Marks for Symbols U+20D0..U+20FF (Extend)
    If cp is greater than or equal to 8400:
        If cp is less than or equal to 8447:
            Return GBP_EXTEND
        End If
    End If
    Note: Regional Indicator Symbols U+1F1E6..U+1F1FF (Regional_Indicator)
    If cp is greater than or equal to 127462:
        If cp is less than or equal to 127487:
            Return GBP_REGIONAL_INDICATOR
        End If
    End If
    Note: Hangul Jamo Initial Consonants (Choseong) U+1100..U+115F (L)
    If cp is greater than or equal to 4352:
        If cp is less than or equal to 4447:
            Return GBP_L
        End If
    End If
    Note: Hangul Jamo Medial Vowels (Jungseong) U+1160..U+11A7 (V)
    If cp is greater than or equal to 4448:
        If cp is less than or equal to 4519:
            Return GBP_V
        End If
    End If
    Note: Hangul Jamo Final Consonants (Jongseong) U+11A8..U+11FF (T)
    If cp is greater than or equal to 4520:
        If cp is less than or equal to 4607:
            Return GBP_T
        End If
    End If
    Note: Hangul Syllables U+AC00..U+D7A3 - LV at every 28th, LVT otherwise
    If cp is greater than or equal to 44032:
        If cp is less than or equal to 55203:
            Let syllable_index be cp minus 44032
            Let t_index be syllable_index minus ((syllable_index divided by 28) multiplied by 28)
            If t_index is equal to 0:
                Return GBP_LV
            End If
            Return GBP_LVT
        End If
    End If
    Note: Extended Pictographic - approximated by main emoji ranges
    If cp is greater than or equal to 127744:
        If cp is less than or equal to 128591:
            Return GBP_EXTENDED_PICTOGRAPHIC
        End If
    End If
    If cp is greater than or equal to 128640:
        If cp is less than or equal to 128767:
            Return GBP_EXTENDED_PICTOGRAPHIC
        End If
    End If
    If cp is greater than or equal to 129280:
        If cp is less than or equal to 129791:
            Return GBP_EXTENDED_PICTOGRAPHIC
        End If
    End If
    If cp is greater than or equal to 129904:
        If cp is less than or equal to 130175:
            Return GBP_EXTENDED_PICTOGRAPHIC
        End If
    End If
    If cp is equal to 169:
        Return GBP_EXTENDED_PICTOGRAPHIC
    End If
    If cp is equal to 174:
        Return GBP_EXTENDED_PICTOGRAPHIC
    End If
    If cp is equal to 8252:
        Return GBP_EXTENDED_PICTOGRAPHIC
    End If
    If cp is equal to 8265:
        Return GBP_EXTENDED_PICTOGRAPHIC
    End If
    Return GBP_OTHER
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: BREAK DECISION
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "grapheme_should_break" takes prev as Integer, curr as Integer, ri_count as Integer, last_was_pictographic_or_zwj as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
        Implements the UAX #29 extended grapheme cluster break rules:
            GB1:  break at start of text (handled by caller)
            GB2:  break at end of text (handled by caller)
            GB3:  do not break CR x LF
            GB4:  break after Control / CR / LF
            GB5:  break before Control / CR / LF
            GB6:  do not break L x (L | V | LV | LVT)
            GB7:  do not break (LV | V) x (V | T)
            GB8:  do not break (LVT | T) x T
            GB9:  do not break x (Extend | ZWJ)
            GB9a: do not break x SpacingMark
            GB9b: do not break Prepend x
            GB11: do not break Extended_Pictographic Extend* ZWJ x Extended_Pictographic
            GB12/13: do not break within an even number of Regional_Indicators
            GB999: otherwise, break
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
        Decision is local to (prev, curr) plus two context flags:
        ri_count = count of consecutive RI codepoints in current cluster,
        last_was_pictographic_or_zwj = 1 if the prior cluster head was
        an extended pictographic that has only seen Extend* ZWJ since.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
        Constant time. The rule order is chosen so most ASCII text
        falls through GB999 immediately.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
        Conservative: when a rule combination is ambiguous, prefers
        to break (over-segmentation), which never corrupts data.
    @End Security_Scope

    Note: GB3
    If prev is equal to GBP_CR:
        If curr is equal to GBP_LF:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If
    Note: GB4
    If prev is equal to GBP_CONTROL:
        Return 1
    End If
    If prev is equal to GBP_CR:
        Return 1
    End If
    If prev is equal to GBP_LF:
        Return 1
    End If
    Note: GB5
    If curr is equal to GBP_CONTROL:
        Return 1
    End If
    If curr is equal to GBP_CR:
        Return 1
    End If
    If curr is equal to GBP_LF:
        Return 1
    End If
    Note: GB6
    If prev is equal to GBP_L:
        If curr is equal to GBP_L:
            Return 0
        End If
        If curr is equal to GBP_V:
            Return 0
        End If
        If curr is equal to GBP_LV:
            Return 0
        End If
        If curr is equal to GBP_LVT:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If
    Note: GB7
    If prev is equal to GBP_LV:
        If curr is equal to GBP_V:
            Return 0
        End If
        If curr is equal to GBP_T:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If
    If prev is equal to GBP_V:
        If curr is equal to GBP_V:
            Return 0
        End If
        If curr is equal to GBP_T:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If
    Note: GB8
    If prev is equal to GBP_LVT:
        If curr is equal to GBP_T:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If
    If prev is equal to GBP_T:
        If curr is equal to GBP_T:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If
    Note: GB9: do not break before Extend or ZWJ
    If curr is equal to GBP_EXTEND:
        Return 0
    End If
    If curr is equal to GBP_ZWJ:
        Return 0
    End If
    Note: GB9a: do not break before SpacingMark
    If curr is equal to GBP_SPACINGMARK:
        Return 0
    End If
    Note: GB9b: do not break after Prepend
    If prev is equal to GBP_PREPEND:
        Return 1
    End If
    Note: GB11: ExtPict + Extend* + ZWJ x ExtPict
    If prev is equal to GBP_ZWJ:
        If last_was_pictographic_or_zwj is equal to 1:
            If curr is equal to GBP_EXTENDED_PICTOGRAPHIC:
                Return 0
            End If
        End If
    End If
    Note: GB12/13: between RI of an odd-then-even pair
    If prev is equal to GBP_REGIONAL_INDICATOR:
        If curr is equal to GBP_REGIONAL_INDICATOR:
            Let parity_check be ri_count minus ((ri_count divided by 2) multiplied by 2)
            If parity_check is equal to 1:
                Return 0
            End If
        End If
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: GRAPHEME CONSTRUCTION
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "grapheme_create" takes data as Integer, byte_length as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Allocates a Grapheme header and copies byte_length bytes from data.
    If byte_length is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let header be allocate(GRAPHEME_HEADER_SIZE)
    If header is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If byte_length is equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_pointer(header, GRAPHEME_OFFSET_DATA, 0)
        Memory.memory_set_integer(header, GRAPHEME_OFFSET_LENGTH, 0)
        Return header
    End If
    Let buf be allocate(byte_length)
    If buf is equal to 0:
        deallocate(header)
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_copy(buf, data, byte_length)
    Memory.memory_set_pointer(header, GRAPHEME_OFFSET_DATA, buf)
    Memory.memory_set_integer(header, GRAPHEME_OFFSET_LENGTH, byte_length)
    Return header
End Process

Process called "grapheme_destroy" takes g as Integer returns Integer:
    If g is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let data be Memory.memory_get_pointer(g, GRAPHEME_OFFSET_DATA)
    If data is not equal to 0:
        deallocate(data)
    End If
    deallocate(g)
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "grapheme_byte_length" takes g as Integer returns Integer:
    If g is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return Memory.memory_get_integer(g, GRAPHEME_OFFSET_LENGTH)
End Process

Process called "grapheme_data" takes g as Integer returns Integer:
    If g is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return Memory.memory_get_pointer(g, GRAPHEME_OFFSET_DATA)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: GRAPHEME ITERATION
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "grapheme_next_offset" takes str as Integer, str_length as Integer, offset as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
        Returns the byte offset immediately after the end of the
        grapheme cluster that begins at offset. If offset is at or past
        str_length, returns str_length. The result is suitable for
        slicing the source string into grapheme-bounded substrings.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
        State machine over the UAX #29 break properties applied as we
        decode UTF-8 codepoint by codepoint. We start a new cluster at
        offset and consume codepoints until grapheme_should_break is 1.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
        O(k) where k = bytes in the cluster (usually 1-12).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
        Malformed UTF-8 yields a single-byte step so the iteration is
        bounded; callers detect this by inspecting the byte value.
    @End Security_Scope

    If str is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If offset is greater than or equal to str_length:
        Return str_length
    End If
    Let cursor be offset
    Let packed be CP.codepoint_from_utf8_bytes(str, cursor, str_length)
    If packed is less than 0:
        Note: Malformed lead byte - advance one and treat as a cluster.
        Return cursor plus 1
    End If
    Let first_len be CP.codepoint_decode_length(packed)
    Let first_cp be CP.codepoint_decode_value(packed)
    Let prev_gbp be grapheme_break_property(first_cp)
    Set cursor to cursor plus first_len
    Let ri_count be 0
    If prev_gbp is equal to GBP_REGIONAL_INDICATOR:
        Set ri_count to 1
    End If
    Let pict_chain be 0
    If prev_gbp is equal to GBP_EXTENDED_PICTOGRAPHIC:
        Set pict_chain to 1
    End If
    Let scanning be 1
    While scanning is equal to 1:
        If cursor is greater than or equal to str_length:
            Set scanning to 0
        Otherwise:
            Let next_packed be CP.codepoint_from_utf8_bytes(str, cursor, str_length)
            If next_packed is less than 0:
                Set scanning to 0
            Otherwise:
                Let next_len be CP.codepoint_decode_length(next_packed)
                Let next_cp be CP.codepoint_decode_value(next_packed)
                Let next_gbp be grapheme_break_property(next_cp)
                Let break_here be grapheme_should_break(prev_gbp, next_gbp, ri_count, pict_chain)
                If break_here is equal to 1:
                    Set scanning to 0
                Otherwise:
                    Set cursor to cursor plus next_len
                    If next_gbp is equal to GBP_REGIONAL_INDICATOR:
                        Set ri_count to ri_count plus 1
                    Otherwise:
                        Set ri_count to 0
                    End If
                    Note: pict_chain tracks GB11: ExtPict followed by Extend* ZWJ x ExtPict
                    If pict_chain is equal to 1:
                        If next_gbp is equal to GBP_EXTEND:
                            Set pict_chain to 1
                        Otherwise:
                            If next_gbp is equal to GBP_ZWJ:
                                Set pict_chain to 1
                            Otherwise:
                                If next_gbp is equal to GBP_EXTENDED_PICTOGRAPHIC:
                                    Set pict_chain to 1
                                Otherwise:
                                    Set pict_chain to 0
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                    Otherwise:
                        If next_gbp is equal to GBP_EXTENDED_PICTOGRAPHIC:
                            Set pict_chain to 1
                        End If
                    End If
                    Set prev_gbp to next_gbp
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Return cursor
End Process

Process called "grapheme_next" takes str as Integer, str_length as Integer, offset as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
        Returns a freshly allocated Grapheme for the cluster starting at
        offset, or 0 if offset is at end. Caller is responsible for
        destroying the result with grapheme_destroy.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
        Find the next break offset via grapheme_next_offset, then copy
        the byte range into a new Grapheme.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
        Allocates per cluster; use grapheme_next_offset for tight loops
        that only need boundaries.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
        Bounded by str_length; never reads past the input.
    @End Security_Scope

    If str is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If offset is greater than or equal to str_length:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let end_off be grapheme_next_offset(str, str_length, offset)
    Let cluster_len be end_off minus offset
    Let src_ptr be str plus offset
    Return grapheme_create(src_ptr, cluster_len)
End Process

Process called "grapheme_count" takes str as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
        Returns the number of grapheme clusters in a null-terminated
        UTF-8 string. This is the true "visual character count" used
        in column-width and truncation logic. NOT byte count.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
        Walks the string via grapheme_next_offset; each iteration counts
        one cluster.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
        O(total bytes) - one decode + state-machine step per codepoint.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
        Tolerates malformed UTF-8 by treating each malformed byte as
        its own cluster, ensuring the iteration always terminates.
    @End Security_Scope

    If str is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let len be StrCore.string_length(str)
    If len is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let offset be 0
    Let count be 0
    While offset is less than len:
        Let next_off be grapheme_next_offset(str, len, offset)
        If next_off is less than or equal to offset:
            Set offset to offset plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Set offset to next_off
        End If
        Set count to count plus 1
    End While
    Return count
End Process
